  <p>
Based on the lecture by Prof. Harrow, and what you know about quantum mechanics, which of the following equations could possibly be true for <em>some</em> choice of isometry [mathjaxinline]V[/mathjaxinline] and <em>all</em> possible quantum states [mathjaxinline]|\psi \rangle[/mathjaxinline] or [mathjaxinline]\rho[/mathjaxinline]? </p>
  <p>
    <choiceresponse>
      <checkboxgroup>
        <choice correct="true" name="1">
          <text>[mathjaxinline]V|\psi \rangle = |\psi \rangle \otimes |0\rangle[/mathjaxinline]</text>
        </choice>
        <choice correct="false" name="2">
          <text>[mathjaxinline]V|\psi \rangle  = |\psi \rangle \otimes |\psi \rangle[/mathjaxinline]</text>
        </choice>
        <choice correct="false" name="3">
          <text>[mathjaxinline]V|\psi \rangle  = |0 \rangle[/mathjaxinline]</text>
        </choice>
        <choice correct="false" name="4">
          <text>[mathjaxinline]V\rho V^\dagger = -\rho[/mathjaxinline]</text>
        </choice>
        <choice correct="false" name="5">
          <text>[mathjaxinline]V\rho V^\dagger = I[/mathjaxinline]</text>
        </choice>
        <choice correct="true" name="6">
          <text>[mathjaxinline]V\rho V^\dagger = \rho \otimes |0\rangle \langle 0|[/mathjaxinline]</text>
        </choice>
      </checkboxgroup>
    </choiceresponse>
  </p>
</problem>
